      There are two different ways to create a page background.
      The cyoungera one (recommended)..
       + is easy to use
       + has no limitations
       - requires carefully prepared texture
      cOldera one..
       + is able to place more textures around page
       + has filters
       + has frames
       + is able to recolorize a texture
       - has very complicated syntax
       - support only the *.X pictures with many limitations
       - generate the pages in 256 colors, never in directcolor

  dYounger
  ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄa
    Syntax is taken from HTML tag BODY and slightly modified:
      variable1=value1 variable2=value2...
      Everything is case insensitive.
    cVariablesa
      background- name of a background picture
      bgtype    - how to handle picture: wallpaper/center/stretch
      bgcolor   - background color, if it's not covered with picture
      text      - color of common text
      cowriter  - color of text written by cowriter (the same brightness)
      link      - color of emphasized text and links
      strong    - color of strongly emphasized text
    cValuesa
      #rrggbb   - color described by its rgb values, hexadecimally 00..ff
      "words"   - any term in ""
      word      - term without spaces could be entered without ""
    cConstantsa
      Black  = #000000    Green  = #008000
      Silver = #C0C0C0    Lime   = #00FF00
      Gray   = #808080    Olive  = #808000
      White  = #FFFFFF    Yellow = #FFFF00
      Maroon = #800000    Navy   = #000080
      Red    = #FF0000    Blue   = #0000FF
      Purple = #800080    Teal   = #008080
      Fuchsia= #FF00FF    Aqua   = #00FFFF
    cImplicit settinga
      background   =""
      bgtype       =wallpaper
      bgcolor      =black
      text         =silver
      cowriter     =aqua
      link         =yellow
      strong       =white
    cExamplea
      text="white" background="bkg.gif" bgtype=


